# Icon Usage Policy

## Source Priority
- Always prefer icons from the project's iconfont symbol script.
- Do not use temporary Figma asset URLs for icons unless explicitly requested.
- If an icon is missing in iconfont, ask user for the iconfont name first.

## Required Script
- Ensure this script exists in `index.html` before `app.js`:
  - `//at.alicdn.com/t/c/font_5157014_8i50w38y1rc.js`

## Rendering Method
- Use symbol references:
  - `<svg class="icon-symbol" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#icon-..."></use></svg>`
- Reuse `.icon-symbol` base style and component-specific size classes.

## Migration Rule
- When editing existing UI, replace Figma CDN icon URLs with iconfont symbols whenever matching icon names are known.
- Keep interaction/hover behavior unchanged after replacement.

## Validation
- After replacement, verify icon names exactly match iconfont IDs.
- If icon does not render, report the missing name and ask for the correct symbol ID.
